Title: BEG House Africana w Khadijah Siferllah at Gibney 280
Description:
Studio D: Beginner House Africana with Khadijah Siferllah. House Africana is a foundational House dance class rooted in Afro-Diasporic movement and music. Guided by Khadijah, the class blends the groove and footwork of House with influences from West African aesthetics, honoring Black dance, culture, and essence.

Each session begins with an introduction to core House steps that will be the focus of the class. These steps are then drilled with attention to rhythm, technique, and musicality. After drilling, dancers learn a short choreographed sequence that weaves together the House steps while incorporating traditional West African movement. Khadijah verbally credits the specific cultural origins of the steps she introduces. The class wraps with “across-the-floor” exercises, where House and African movement continue to meet—giving dancers a chance to travel, expand, and let loose.

While best suited for Beginner dancers, all levels are welcome. Khadijah creates a warm, open space for exploration and growth, where community and joy are at the center.

Title: Leg Room @ Dead Letter no. 9
Description: Clear your calendar and make space on the dancefloor — Leg Room is taking over Dead Letter No. 9 for a Thursday night filled with infectious beats and endless vibes. This dynamic DJ duo knows how to keep the energy high and the grooves flowing, spinning tracks that’ll have you moving from start to finish.Whether you’re shaking off the workweek or just craving a spontaneous night out, this is your invitation to let loose! There's No cover, no limits — just pure rhythm and a room full of people ready to dance.Come as you are, bring your friends, and lose yourself in the music. The night is young, and the floor is waiting.Free w/ RSVP

Title: The People's Ball: Style is a Revolution
Description: You’re invited to THE PEOPLE’S BALL, Brooklyn Public Library’s free annual celebration of fashion, personal style and inclusivity. THE PEOPLE’S BALL, named Time Out New York’s Best Nightlife Event of 2023, welcomes you to dress up in the clothes that make you feel your most beautiful and authentic and walk the runway and walk the runway in Central Library's iconic lobby. The free event, held on the eve of the Met Gala, offers an alternative to expensive, exclusive galas and showcases the diverse styles that make up New York City's urban runway.
